<article class="container article-container">
    <div class="img-con">
        <img src="/img/geopolitics.jpg" alt="Geopolitics Stock Photos, Royalty Free Geopolitics Images | Depositphotos">
    </div>
    <% if(locals.blogPost) { %>
        <div class="article-title">
            <div class="title-sub">
                <h1>
                    <%= post.title %>
                </h1>
                <p>
                    <%= post.preview %>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="article-message">
            <div class="article-message-main-sub">
                <div class="sub-sub-con">
                    <h2>Recognizing a Sovereign Palestine: Symbolism and Implications</h2>
                    <p>On May 22, the prime ministers of Spain, Norway, and Ireland jointly announced their governments’
                        intention to recognize a sovereign Palestinian state. While largely symbolic, this move carries
                        significant weight, especially given the ongoing conflict between Israel and Hamas in the Gaza
                        Strip.
                        However, the implications extend beyond symbolism.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="article-message-main-sub">
                <div class="sub-sub-con">
                    <h2>Challenges for the Palestinians</h2>
                    <p>Setting aside the moral dimensions, the new legal and political status quo would significantly impact
                        the
                        Palestinians. A sovereign state must ensure neighboring nations’ protection from harms emanating
                        from
                        within its borders. If unable to do so, it faces international consequences, including the use of
                        force.
                        Thus, a nascent Palestinian state could find itself at war with neighboring Israel almost
                        immediately.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="article-message-main-sub">
                <div class="sub-sub-con">
                    <h2>Stripped Subsidies and Economic Realities</h2>
                    <p>Moreover, a sovereign Palestine would lose substantial subsidies provided by Israel. Prior to October
                        7,
                        Israel supplied nearly a third of the Palestinian Territories’ fuel, employed over 100,000 workers
                        directly, and supported tens of thousands more indirectly. These economic ties would be abruptly
                        severed
                        upon statehood.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="article-message-main-sub">
                <div class="sub-sub-con">
                    <h2>North Korea’s Space Activities: Balancing Sovereignty and Security</h2>
                    <p>Meanwhile, North Korea’s space activities have sparked tensions among global powers. U.N. Assistant
                        Secretary-General Khaled Khiari emphasized that sovereign states have the right to benefit from
                        peaceful
                        space endeavors. However, North Korea’s actions—launches and threats related to nuclear weapons—have
                        raised concerns. Striking the delicate balance between sovereignty and security remains a challenge.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="article-message-main-sub">
                <div class="sub-sub-con">
                    <h2>Civil Society’s Role in Shaping the Future</h2>
                    <p>Civil society leaders recently converged in Nairobi, Kenya, envisioning a people’s agenda for the UN
                        Summit of the Future. As states grapple with complex issues, civil society’s ambition and advocacy
                        play
                        a crucial role in shaping multilateral solutions.</p>
                    <p>Stay tuned for our full blog post, where we’ll delve deeper into these topics and explore the
                        intricate
                        dance between sovereignty, security, and global cooperation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        <% } else { %>
            <h1>nothing to see here. <a href="/">Go back</a></h1>
            <% } %>

</article>